==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French [[empostume]], alteration of [[apostume]] ‘apostume, large abcess’, from Latin [[apostema]], from Greek [[αποστεμα]] ‘separation of pus into an abcess’, from [[αποστηναι]] ‘withdraw’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ɪm'pɒstju:m/

===Noun===
'''impostume'''
# an [[abscess]]